# 🏝️ Day 3 - Treasure Island

A fun text-based adventure game built with Python as part of the **100 Days of Code** challenge.

The player navigates through a series of choices in search of a hidden treasure. The game uses simple `if`/`else` logic to create an interactive story experience.

## 🚀 Features

- Interactive story with multiple choices
- Beginner-friendly `if/elif/else` structure
- Emphasizes logical thinking and branching

## 🛠️ Built With

- Python 3

## 🧠 What I Practiced

- Conditional statements
- User input handling
- Game flow control

---

Part of the [100 Days of Code](https://github.com/Synel96/100-Days-Of-Code) journey.
